<p>I write my own InputFormat for the Apache Hive. I inherited my input format class from <code>org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.InputFormat</code></p>  <p>When I execute select from my table, I get the error: <code>FAILED: SemanticException 1:14 Input format must implement InputFormat. Error encountered near token 'some_table_name'</code></p>  <p>View Hive sources showed that InputFormat must implement the interface of the old api: <code>org.apache.hadoop.mapred.InputFormat</code></p>  <p>Is there a way to use the new mapreduce API to the Hive?</p>